    "SUMMARY": "Jónas Þór Næs (born 27 December 1986) is a Faroese retired international footballer.\nHe played professionally for BK Frem in 2005-06 and again 2009–10. Næs previously played for Valur (2011–13), Fremad Amager (2007–08), Køge BK (2008–09), Argja Bóltfelag (2007), NSÍ Runavík (2008) and B36 (2013-16)."
